## This commit (stage 8/10: annotation queues — NEW PR this round)
Full annotation-queues subsystem replicating CH observable behavior:
- One mutable record per queue/item id with deleted_at tombstones (the
  CH lightweight-update model), stores initialized in stage 1.
- Global item state is argMax-by-updated_at across per-annotator
  transition rows; _item_progress_state returns ('unstarted', '') for
  untouched items — '' not None, because the CH column is a String with
  default '' (tests assert annotator_user_id == '').
- Item positions via ROW_NUMBER assigned BEFORE pagination.
- Error message must contain 'Invalid state transition' (tests match
  substring).
- annotation_queue_add_calls duplicates semantics: re-adding a call that
  already has a live item is a no-op for that call.

